1.text: Divide your hair into 2 even sections.

2.text: Take a thin strand of hair from the left section.

3.text: Pull the thin strand up and across the left section.

4.text: Tuck the thin strand under the right section.

5.text: Tug gently on the 2 sections to tighten them.

6.text: Take a thin strand from the right section.

7.text: Pull the thin strand up and across the right section.

8.text: Tuck it under the left section.

9.text: Keep alternating sides until you reach the end of your hair.

10.text: Wrap a hair tie around the end of your hair.

11.text: Create a tousled braid by rubbing it between your hands.

12.text: Gather up a section of hair at the crown of your head.

14.text: Pull up a thin strand from the left side of your head.

15.text: Pull the thin strand across the left section and towards the right.

16.text: Tuck the thin strand under the right section.

17.text: Pull a thin strand of hair from the right side of your head.

18.text: Pull it across the right section and towards the left.

19.text: Tuck the thin strand under the left section.

20.text: Pull up a new center section.

21.text: Keep alternating sides until you reach the base of your head.

22.text: Continue braiding your hair in the fishtail fashion.

23.text: Tie the braid off towards the end.

24.text: Create a messy fishtail braid by gently tugging on the edges.

25.text: Find some thin hair elastics that match your hair color.

26.text: Pull your hair into a low ponytail.

28.text: Tie another elastic around your hair a few inches down from the first 1.

30.text: Keep doing this until you have only a few inches of your hair left.

33.text: Try making a topsy-turvy ponytail before you start doing the fishtail braid.

34.text: Use a clip or barrette to cover up the hair tie.

35.text: Roll your braid into a bun at the nape of your neck.

36.text: Add some colored hair extensions before you start braiding your hair.
